# Infrastructure-as-Code: AWS Configuration

This document outlines the current Terraform-managed infrastructure for VaultPay's storage layer. It highlights the configurations flagged in the [Q3 External Penetration Test Report].

## Resource: S3 Bucket (KYC Storage)

hcl
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "customer_docs" {
  bucket = "vaultpay-customer-docs-prod"
  acl    = "private"

  tags = {
    Environment = "prod"
    DataClass   = "PII"
    Owner       = "Compliance"
  }
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket_policy" "allow_access" {
  bucket = aws_s3_bucket.customer_docs.id
  policy = data.aws_iam_policy_document.allow_access.json
}

data "aws_iam_policy_document" "allow_access" {
  statement {
    principals {
      type        = "*"
      identifiers = ["*"]
    }

    actions = [
      "s3:GetObject",
    ]

    resources = [
      aws_s3_bucket.customer_docs.arn,
      "${aws_s3_bucket.customer_docs.arn}/*",
    ]
  }
}


## Current S3 Inventory & Exposure Status

| Bucket Name | Purpose | Public Access Block | Policy Status | Logging |
|-------------|---------|---------------------|---------------|---------|
| `vaultpay-static-assets` | Web UI Assets | Disabled | Public-Read | Enabled |
| `vaultpay-customer-docs-prod` | KYC Documents | Enabled | **Overly Permissive** | Enabled |
| `vaultpay-audit-logs` | SOC2 Logs | Enabled | Restricted | Enabled |
| `vaultpay-terraform-state` | IaC State | Enabled | Restricted | Disabled |
| `vaultpay-temp-exports` | CSV Exports | Disabled | **Public-Read** | Disabled |
| `vaultpay-backups-db` | DB Snapshots | Enabled | Restricted | Enabled |
| `vaultpay-internal-wiki` | Internal Docs | Enabled | Restricted | Enabled |
| `vaultpay-lambda-code` | Functions | Enabled | Restricted | Enabled |

## IAM Role: Web-API-Runner

This role is used by the Core-API to interact with AWS services. It currently has excessive permissions.


{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:ListBucket",
        "s3:GetObject",
        "s3:PutObject"
      ],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::vaultpay-customer-docs-prod",
        "arn:aws:s3:::vaultpay-customer-docs-prod/*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": "kms:*",
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}


## Remediation Plan

1. Modify `aws_iam_policy_document.allow_access` to remove the wildcard principal.
2. Restrict `s3:GetObject` to the `Web-API-Runner` role ARN specifically.
3. Enable `aws_s3_bucket_public_access_block` for all buckets except `static-assets`.

---

**See Also:** [Q3 External Penetration Test Report — VaultPay], [Core-API Repository — README & Snippets], [Security Operations Runbook — Incident Response & Hardening]
